The '''[[Fallowfield]] Loop railway line''' was a local [[railway]] route in [[Greater Manchester]], [[England]]. Trains on the [[Manchester, Sheffield and Lincolnshire Railway]] line (later, the [[Great Central Railway]] line) used the 'Loop' to connect to [[Manchester Central railway station]] (now the [[Manchester Central (Conference Centre)|Manchester Central conference centre]]).
<br />
It was built in 1891 and closed in 1988.

